  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 33.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Meremoth the son of Uriah, or Urijah",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", was one of the heads of the priestly order, both under Ezra and under Nehemiah. He is mentioned as repairing two pieces of the wall of Jerusalem when Nehemiah was governor (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 3:4, 21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and also as one of those who set their seal to the covenant with God which the whole people entered into, under Ezra's and Nehemiah's guidance, shortly after the completion of the wall, in  ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "date",
        "text": "B.C. 444",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Eleazar the son of Phinehas",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is perhaps the Eleazar mentioned as taking part in the dedication of the wall (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 12:42",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Like Meremoth, he was a priest. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Jozabad and Noadiah",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", chief Levites, occur again in ch. 10:23, and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 8:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 10:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; and Nehemiah 12:3. Ezra 8:33",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "They arrived at Jerusalem, as stated ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 7:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", on the first day of the fifth month, the journey consequently occupying three months and a half. The particulars of the journey are not communicated; and as we do not even know the locality of the place of meeting at the river Ahava, the length of road to be traversed cannot be determined. After their arrival at Jerusalem, they abode, i.e., remained, as Nehemiah subsequently did, quiet and inactive three days, to recover from the fatigues and hardships of the journey, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 2:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", before they undertook the arrangement of their affairs. On the fourth day, the gifts they had brought with them were delivered in the house of God (נשׁקל, like אשׁקלה, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 8:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") into the hand of Meremoth and Eleazar the priests, and Jozabad and Noadiah, two Levites, who took charge of them, the chiefs of the priests and Levites being, according to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 8:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", also present. Meremoth Ben Uriah reappears in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 3:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 3:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and is also intended ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 12:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Eleazar the son of Phinehas, and the Levite Noadiah, are not again met with. Jozabad, of the sons of Jeshua (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 2:40",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), may be the Levite Jozabad mentioned ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 10:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Binnui is named among the Levites, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 10:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 12:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
